Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Put the @sweetcorn ribs{1} onto a large piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil. Scrunch to enclose, then pop the parcel onto one half of a lightly oiled #baking tray{}.

Cut the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then cut into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop onto another baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, cook the chips on the top shelf until golden and the corn ribs on the middle shelf until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn the chips halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Halve the @glazed burger buns{2}.

Open the @pineapple rings{1} tin and pour 1 tsp of pineapple juice per person into a #medium bowl{}. Add a drizzle of oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well, then set your pineapple dressing aside.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the garlic, @Caribbean style Jerk seasoning{2}, @panko breadcrumbs{10}, @water{2%tbsp} and @salt{¼%tsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the corn has been cooking for ~{8-10%minutes}, remove the tray from the oven and add the burgers to the other side.

Bake for the remaining time until everything is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Remove the pineapple rings from the tin, then lay them into the hot pan. Cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn only every 1-2 mins.

Once charred, set 1 whole pineapple ring per person, then cut the rest into chunks.

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of them and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}. At the same time, pop the buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When the corn is ready, remove it from the oven and spread over the @unsalted butter{20%g}. Season with salt and pepper.

Just before serving, add the pineapple chunks and half the @wild rocket{20} to the pineapple dressing. Toss to coat.

Stack a cheesy burger on the bun bases, then top with the reserved pineapple ring and the remaining rocket. Spread the @mayonnaise{32%g} on the bun lid and sandwich together.

Serve your craft burger with the chips, buttery corn ribs and salad alongside. Enjoy!